## Dimension: Atomicity

**Definition**: The degree to which each claim expresses exactly one indivisible proposition.

**Why This Matters**: In Delphi rounds, experts must be able to accept, reject, or qualify individual claims. Compound claims ("X and Y") prevent this granularity and force all-or-nothing responses.

